    "Recent progress in the field of AI enables models to not only analyze image data but also integrate clinical information, including patient demographics and past medical history (4) (5) (6).",
    "Advancements allow for the simultaneous evaluation and identification of multiple lesions from wide-field images (7, 8).",
    "Moreover, models can now gain information from whole slide images without having to use costly pixel-wise human-made annotations (9).",
    "Despite these advancements, research has found that AI models lack robustness to simple data variations, have proven inadequate in real-world dermatologic practice performance, and that barriers remain before achieving clinical readiness (2, (10) (11) (12) (13) (14).",
